with flaky pie crust and creamy chicken pot pie filling.  Classic comfort food!","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#primaryimage","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550.jpg","contentUrl":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550.jpg","width":550,"height":550,"caption":"Slice of the best homemade chicken pot pie"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Main Dish","item":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/category/entree/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"The Best Classic Chicken Pot Pie"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/#website","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/","name":"The Wholesome Dish","description":"Easy Recipes for Busy Families","publisher":{"@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/#organization","name":"The Wholesome Dish","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/#/schema/logo/image/","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/organization-logo.jpg","contentUrl":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/organization-logo.jpg","width":796,"height":226,"caption":"The Wholesome Dish"},"image":{"@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/#/schema/logo/image/"},"sameAs":["https://www.facebook.com/thewholesomedish/","https://www.instagram.com/the_wholesome_dish/","https://www.pinterest.com/thewholesomedish","https://www.tiktok.com/@amandafinksofficial"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/#/schema/person/2c6befc6299adcb6ba10e82c5e3753c9","name":"Amanda Finks","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/#/schema/person/image/","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f6189ce30ef516a4e69d0d22cdd9ee3e36b1d617597a0bcac2ae1d551c33c825?s=96&d=mm&r=pg","contentUrl":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f6189ce30ef516a4e69d0d22cdd9ee3e36b1d617597a0bcac2ae1d551c33c825?s=96&d=mm&r=pg","caption":"Amanda Finks"},"description":"I’m a Registered Dietitian Nutritionist living in Zionsville, IN. I’m an avid cook, travel nerd, &amp; lover of good food! I’m trained in Food Science &amp; recipe development. It’s my mission to bring you the BEST recipes your whole family will love!","sameAs":["https://www.thewholesomedish.com/about-me/"]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"The Best Classic Chicken Pot Pie Recipe","author":{"@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/#/schema/person/2c6befc6299adcb6ba10e82c5e3753c9"},"description":"The Best Classic Chicken Pot Pie Recipe - Homemade chicken pot pie with flaky pie crust and creamy chicken pot pie filling. &nbsp;Classic comfort food!","datePublished":"2018-09-14T17:52:57+00:00","image":["https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550.jpg","https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550-500x500.jpg","https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550-500x375.jpg","https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Best Classic Chicken Pot Pie Recipe","description":"The Best Chicken Pot Pie with creamy homemade filling.","thumbnailUrl":"https://content.jwplatform.com/thumbs/LQX2rd4N-720.jpg","contentUrl":"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/LQX2rd4N.mp4","uploadDate":"2019-09-10T18:23:19.000Z","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["8","8 slices"],"prepTime":"PT20M","cookTime":"PT30M","totalTime":"PT50M","recipeIngredient":["4 tablespoons unsalted butter","1 lb. boneless skinless chicken breast (-cut into small bite size pieces)","1 cup sliced carrots","1/2 cup sliced celery","1/2 cup chopped yellow onion","1 1/4 teaspoons salt","1/2 teaspoon garlic powder","1/2 teaspoon dried thyme leaves","1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper","1/4 cup all-purpose flour","1/2 cup heavy cream","1 cup chicken broth","1/2 cup frozen peas","2 tablespoons minced fresh flat-leaf parsley","2 (1 top and 1 bottom) unbaked pie crusts  ((could use pre-made refrigerated - 1 box))"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Make sure there is an oven rack on the bottom rack of the oven.  Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.","name":"Make sure there is an oven rack on the bottom rack of the oven.  Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#wprm-recipe-8911-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the butter to a large skillet over medium heat.  Once the butter is melted, add the chicken, carrots, celery, onion, salt, garlic powder, thyme leaves, and pepper.  Cook for 8-10 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through, stirring often.","name":"Add the butter to a large skillet over medium heat.  Once the butter is melted, add the chicken, carrots, celery, onion, salt, garlic powder, thyme leaves, and pepper.  Cook for 8-10 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through, stirring often.","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#wprm-recipe-8911-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the flour.  Stir well, until no dry flour remains.  Slowly stir in the cream, then the chicken broth.  Cook until bubbling and thick, stirring often, 3-4 minutes.","name":"Add the flour.  Stir well, until no dry flour remains.  Slowly stir in the cream, then the chicken broth.  Cook until bubbling and thick, stirring often, 3-4 minutes.","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#wprm-recipe-8911-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove from the heat.  Stir in the peas and flat leaf parsley.  Let this cool for 15-30 minutes before filling the pie.*","name":"Remove from the heat.  Stir in the peas and flat leaf parsley.  Let this cool for 15-30 minutes before filling the pie.*","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#wprm-recipe-8911-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Fit one pie crust into a 9-inch pie plate.  Spoon the cooled filling into the pie crust.  Top with the second pie crust.  Seal the edges of the pie crust together.  Cut 3-4 slits in the top crust to allow steam to escape.","name":"Fit one pie crust into a 9-inch pie plate.  Spoon the cooled filling into the pie crust.  Top with the second pie crust.  Seal the edges of the pie crust together.  Cut 3-4 slits in the top crust to allow steam to escape.","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#wprm-recipe-8911-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the filled pie plate on a baking sheet.  Bake for 30 minutes on the bottom rack of the oven.","name":"Place the filled pie plate on a baking sheet.  Bake for 30 minutes on the bottom rack of the oven.","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#wprm-recipe-8911-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cool for 15-30 minutes before slicing and serving.**","name":"Cool for 15-30 minutes before slicing and serving.**","url":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#wprm-recipe-8911-step-0-6"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.99","ratingCount":"480","reviewCount":"18"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Best ever!!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kristen Mueller"},"datePublished":"2025-08-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Love this pot pie, I have made it at least 10 times.  I have tinkered a little, I only use 1/4 t of thyme,\r\nand will sub 1% milk if I have no cream.  \r\n\r\nThank you for this recipe, it's amazing..\r\nTry it, you will not be disappointed.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Wombatsrule"},"datePublished":"2025-08-18"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is the best chicken pot pie I have ever had - my family asks me to make it all the time - thank you for the recipe!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"KLM"},"datePublished":"2025-08-09"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was so yummy. My husband couldn't get enough!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lynda"},"datePublished":"2025-07-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"She said she wanted to make the best chicken pot pie recipe. Well in my opinion, she did it. This recipe is fantastic and is truly the best chicken pot pie I've ever had. Savings the recipe for future use for sure.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Steve Jake"},"datePublished":"2025-06-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was the first Chicken Pot Pie that I ever made and it was nothing less than outstanding! Substituted milk for heavy cream and it still came out great! Decreased salt to 1t. For later efforts, egg washed the crust  lightly and heated 10-12 minutes before adding the filling. (egg wash-1 egg, 1 T water or milk, pinch of salt). Very difficult to cover crust edges, but did it.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"David Bobke"},"datePublished":"2025-05-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I followed exactly and it was excellent. I had to make the filling the night before and worried it would have absorbed the moisture, it did not. No leftovers!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kathleen McDade"},"datePublished":"2025-05-09"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"A family favorite!  The only thing I do differently is to add some diced potatoes. It thickens up the filling, and fills up the kids!!  Thanks for sharing!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Karen Melton"},"datePublished":"2025-05-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is so delicious! My 9YO grandson keeps asking me to make it. I substitute the chopped onions with a cup of frozen pearl onions. Thank you for the recipe!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Donna B"},"datePublished":"2025-04-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was delicious! I’ll be keeping this recipe forever- such good comfort food! Thanks so much.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lisa Lefebvre"},"datePublished":"2025-04-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️\r\n\r\nMade this chicken pot pie, very easy and very delicious","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Brown David A"},"datePublished":"2025-03-30"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"The best chicken pot pie by far, my 7 year old boy is super fussy but he eats this like there is no tomorrow.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Tara"},"datePublished":"2025-03-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is my favorite chicken pot pie recipe. :) I come back to it over and over again! I’ve used it for years!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sydney"},"datePublished":"2025-03-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Delicious!  I used rotesserie  chicken, added canned potatoe and used a spoonful of better than bouillon paste to pump up the flavors along with a little adobe seasoning and egg washed the crust!  Only problem, no leftovers!   New family favorite!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Arline"},"datePublished":"2025-03-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"ABSOLUTELY the BEST chicken pot pie I have ever had. Followed your recipe exactly except that I used frozen pearl onions instead of chopped onions, used boneless chicken thighs instead of breast, and added a pinch of truffle salt at the end. Delicious to the last crumb.\r\nI used store-bought frozen crusts (M.Cal.) &amp; sprinkled top crust with a little water, then kneaded it into a ball, flattened it out, &amp; rolled it into a disc that fit the top perfectly. My previous experiences in trying to flatten the top  crusts out have always ended up with cracked messes.\r\nThank you for my new favorite chicken pot pie recipe.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Richard Schinella"},"datePublished":"2025-02-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is definitely a family favorite. In fact, I buy rotisserie chickens exclusively for this recipe! Lol.  Prepping the crust and the filling truly takes it to the next level!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Leah"},"datePublished":"2025-02-13"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"have been looking for a great filling recipe for a very long time and this is the one.  thank you.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"coby l morris weber"},"datePublished":"2025-01-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Can I use left-over grilled chicken?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Luisa Martins"},"datePublished":"2025-01-27"}],"recipeCategory":["Dinner","Entree","Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"keywords":"best chicken pot pie, chicken pot pie recipe, homemade chicken pot pie","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 /8th of the recipe","calories":"419 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"30 g","proteinContent":"16 g","fatContent":"25 g","saturatedFatContent":"11 g","cholesterolContent":"71 mg","sodiumContent":"755 mg","fiberContent":"2 g","sugarContent":"1 g"},"@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/"}]}</script>
