.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20550%20550'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="shared-counts-hidden-image" data-pin-description="The Best Classic Chicken Pot Pie" data-pin-media="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550.jpg" alt="" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550.jpg" /><noscript><img width="550" height="550" decoding="async" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550.jpg" class="shared-counts-hidden-image" data-pin-description="The Best Classic Chicken Pot Pie" data-pin-media="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-550.jpg" alt="" /></noscript></div><p>The Best Classic Chicken Pot Pie Recipe &#8211; Homemade chicken pot pie with flaky pie crust and creamy chicken pot pie filling.  Classic comfort food!</p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8908" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-600-X-900.jpg" alt="Slice of the best chicken pot pie recipe with creamy filling inside pie crust" width="600" height="900" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-600-X-900.jpg 600w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-600-X-900-400x600.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p>This chicken pot pie recipe is loaded with flavor.  It&#8217;s got flaky pie crust and a buttery creamy chicken pot pie filling with chicken breast, a mix of fresh and frozen vegetables, and a mix of dried and fresh herbs.</p>
<p>I initially wanted to make an easy chicken pot pie.  So, I started out using refrigerated pie dough, all frozen vegetables, and all dried herbs.  That was easy, but it really needed some bright fresh flavors.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8906" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20680%20530'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Homemade chicken pot pie in a pie plate with one piece taken out showing the creamy filling" width="680" height="530" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-7.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-7-400x312.jpg 400w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-7.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8906" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-7.jpg" alt="Homemade chicken pot pie in a pie plate with one piece taken out showing the creamy filling" width="680" height="530" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-7.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-7-400x312.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></noscript></p>
<p>So, instead of making the easiest recipe, I decided to make the BEST chicken pot pie recipe.</p>
<p>Using fresh vegetables and some fresh herbs in the filling gives this pot pie so much flavor that it&#8217;s ok to take a short-cut with the crust and use a pre-made refrigerated pie crust.</p>
<p>Of course, if you have the time to make your own homemade pie crust, that would be amazing too.</p>
<h2>How to make chicken pot pie:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Melt butter in a large skillet.</li>
<li>Add chicken, carrots, celery, and onion.</li>
<li>Add salt, garlic powder, dried thyme, and pepper.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8916" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20680%20429'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="chicken breast, carrots, celery, onions, butter, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and dried thyme leaves in a skillet" width="680" height="429" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-10.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-10-400x252.jpg 400w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-10.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8916" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-10.jpg" alt="chicken breast, carrots, celery, onions, butter, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and dried thyme leaves in a skillet" width="680" height="429" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-10.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-10-400x252.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></noscript></p>
<ul>
<li>Cook for 8-10 minutes.</li>
<li>Stir in flour.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8917" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20680%20438'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Stirring flour into butter, chicken, and vegetables" width="680" height="438" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-11.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-11-400x258.jpg 400w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-11.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8917" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-11.jpg" alt="Stirring flour into butter, chicken, and vegetables" width="680" height="438" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-11.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-11-400x258.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></noscript></p>
<ul>
<li>Stir in cream until smooth.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8918" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20680%20430'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Stirring heavy whipping cream into a roux with chicken and vegetables" width="680" height="430" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-12.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-12-400x253.jpg 400w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-12.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8918" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-12.jpg" alt="Stirring heavy whipping cream into a roux with chicken and vegetables" width="680" height="430" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-12.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-12-400x253.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></noscript></p>
<ul>
<li>Stir in chicken broth until smooth.</li>
<li>Cook until bubbling and thick.</li>
<li>Add peas and parsley to the filling.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8919" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20680%20417'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Adding peas and minced fresh parsley into creamy chicken pot pie filling" width="680" height="417" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-13.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-13-400x245.jpg 400w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-13.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8919" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-13.jpg" alt="Adding peas and minced fresh parsley into creamy chicken pot pie filling" width="680" height="417" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-13.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-13-400x245.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></noscript></p>
<ul>
<li>Cool.</li>
<li>Fit the bottom pie crust into a pie plate.</li>
<li>Spoon the creamy filling into the bottom crust.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8920" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20680%20472'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Adding homemade creamy chicken pot pie filling to a pie crust in a pie plate" width="680" height="472" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-14.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-14-400x278.jpg 400w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-14.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8920" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-14.jpg" alt="Adding homemade creamy chicken pot pie filling to a pie crust in a pie plate" width="680" height="472" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-14.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-14-400x278.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></noscript></p>
<ul>
<li>Place the top crust over the filling.</li>
<li>Seal the edges of the crust and cut slits in the top crust.</li>
<li>Place the pie on a baking sheet (I line mine with aluminum foil in case the filling bubbles over).</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8922" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20680%20402'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Unbaked chicken pot pie on a baking sheet" width="680" height="402" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-16.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-16-400x236.jpg 400w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-16.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8922" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-16.jpg" alt="Unbaked chicken pot pie on a baking sheet" width="680" height="402" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-16.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Chicken-Pot-Pie-Recipe-16-400x236.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></noscript></p>
<ul>
<li>Bake.</li>
<li>Cool before slicing.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8905" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20680%20524'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Slice of classic chicken pot pie with pie crust and creamy filling" width="680" height="524" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-4.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-4-400x308.jpg 400w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-4.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8905" src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-4.jpg" alt="Slice of classic chicken pot pie with pie crust and creamy filling" width="680" height="524" srcset="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-4.jpg 680w, https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Best-Classic-Chicken-Pot-Pie-4-400x308.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></noscript></p>
