									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Delicious!  I used rotesserie  chicken, added canned potatoe and used a spoonful of better than bouillon paste to pump up the flavors along with a little adobe seasoning and egg washed the crust!  Only problem, no leftovers!   New family favorite!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-183686" data-commentid="183686" data-postid="8904" data-belowelement="div-comment-183686" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Arline" aria-label="Reply to Arline">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-183503" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-183503" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Richard Schinella</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/comment-page-30/#comment-183503"><time datetime="2025-02-21T17:56:36-06:00">February 21, 2025 at 5:56 PM</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
ABSOLUTELY the BEST chicken pot pie I have ever had. Followed your recipe exactly except that I used frozen pearl onions instead of chopped onions, used boneless chicken thighs instead of breast, and added a pinch of truffle salt at the end. Delicious to the last crumb.<br />
I used store-bought frozen crusts (M.Cal.) &amp; sprinkled top crust with a little water, then kneaded it into a ball, flattened it out, &amp; rolled it into a disc that fit the top perfectly. My previous experiences in trying to flatten the top  crusts out have always ended up with cracked messes.<br />
Thank you for my new favorite chicken pot pie recipe.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-183503" data-commentid="183503" data-postid="8904" data-belowelement="div-comment-183503" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Richard Schinella" aria-label="Reply to Richard Schinella">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-183441" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-183441" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Leah</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/comment-page-30/#comment-183441"><time datetime="2025-02-13T17:45:04-06:00">February 13, 2025 at 5:45 PM</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
This is definitely a family favorite. In fact, I buy rotisserie chickens exclusively for this recipe! Lol.  Prepping the crust and the filling truly takes it to the next level!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-183441" data-commentid="183441" data-postid="8904" data-belowelement="div-comment-183441" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Leah" aria-label="Reply to Leah">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-183307" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-183307" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">coby l morris weber</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/the-best-classic-chicken-pot-pie/comment-page-30/#comment-183307"><time datetime="2025-01-28T11:41:55-06:00">January 28, 2025 at 11:41 AM</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.thewholesomedish.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
have been looking for a great filling recipe for a very long time and this is the one.  thank you.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-183307" data-commentid="183307" data-postid="8904" data-belowelement="div-comment-183307" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to coby l morris weber" aria-label="Reply to coby l morris weber">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		</ol><!-- .comment-list -->
